Meanwhile, Fletcher hangs out with Chyna's dad in order to get on his good side.

Fletcher thinks Chyna is talking about him and tells Chyna to ask him out. After Chyna invites Nigel to go roller skating, Fletcher gets jealous and, along with Angus, devises a plan to sabotage Chyna's date. Meanwhile, Darryl challenges Olive and Cameron to see who can get the highest score on an ...

9.title: ClairvoyANT
9.plot: After Principal Skidmore gives every student in school an award for their talent except Cameron, Chyna sets out to help him realize his talent. When she comes up short, Chyna convinces Cameron that he is psychic and now everyone in school is listening to Cameron's predictions and Chyna has to keep making those predictions come true. Meanwhile, Fletcher takes a stand against Principal Skidmore when she replaces the dinosaur-shaped chicken nuggets in the cafeteria.

10.plot: Cameron pretends to be Chyna's manager when they meet hip-hop producer, Hippo. Chyna thinks it might be her big break, but when Hippo wants to make some changes that Chyna doesn't agree with, it's up to Cameron to step in and save the day. Meanwhile, Olive and Fletcher are on opposing teams of a Home Economics class challenge.

Meanwhile, Cameron has to help Lexi out of a bind after she unfairly wins a beauty pageant.

But when Zanko passes the painting off as his own at his comeback party, Chyna creates an elite team to rescue the painting. Meanwhile, Paisley and Lexi audition to be a princess for a kid's birthday party and Paisley gets the part.

13.title: The ReplacemANT
13.plot: When Olive takes over as the new history teacher, Chyna advises her to show everyone who's in charge. That advice quickly backfires when Olive sends Lexi and Chyna to detention, now the two former rivals must team up to get rid of "Ms. Doyle".

However, when the ANTs go on a field trip to a fortune cookie factory, Chyna realizes she lost Goo Goo's number. So Olive, Fletcher and Angus help retrace Chyna's steps back to the factory to find the misplaced number. Meanwhile, Lexi finds out she wasn't invited to a fellow cheerleaders birthday party.

Only to have Angus buy everything off the truck.

A girl is excepted into the A.N.T. Program at her brothers high school. She meets two other young prodigies of the A.N.T. Program and together they go through many stages. They are put up against a bully named Lexi, the most popular girl in school. Between being in high school with everybody older then them and having incredible talents, they face the odds together even a new school to suit all of their prodigetical needs away from Their old school principal.
